		<text>
		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p>mostly yiddish German</p>
		  <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#45;On <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> day of Rosh Hodesh</date></p>
		    <p rend="indent(3)"><date>of second Adar&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;1848&#63;</date></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">To my beloved&#44; my loyal friend&#44; full of good<lb/> qualites etc. <persName>Eliezer</persName>&#45;may he live forever<lb/> I have come with this letter to fulfill<lb/> your request&#44; and to write out in order<lb/> the prayer&#44; &#34;God full of mercy&#34;<lb/> &#40;[&#41;Here follows the Hishkaba&#40;]&#41;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Evidently&#44; my dear&#44; you have for&#45;<lb/>gotten that I wrote to you at the end<lb/> of last year that my circumstances<lb/> do not permit me to continue to receive the<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Kol Ya&#45;a&#45;kob</hi>.  I shall therefore take<lb/> up the copies you have sent me so far<lb/> until I can safely return them to you.<lb/>  I <del>shall</del> want to receive the &#34;<hi rend="underline">Zir Ne&#45;e&#45;<lb/>man</hi>&#34;.  but will not pay the money in<lb/> advance since usually such works<lb/> are begun but never completed.<lb/>  <del>Thus&#44; for example&#44;</del> I think you</p>

		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p>will agree with me in this matter.  I paid<lb/> for the Kos Ye&#45;shu&#45;oth&#44; and to this day no<lb/> more than ten installments have appeared though<lb/> there should have been twelve of them.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I really pained by the fact that<lb/> <persName>Mister Pope</persName> has not sent you his speeches<lb/> For&#44; my dearly beloved&#44; to you I reveal my<lb/> heart and soul.  I tremble because I have<lb/> to preach every <date>Sabbath</date>&#44; and a man like<lb/> me&#44; who has troubles private and public&#44;<lb/> must very often rely upon outside aid<lb/> in order to be able to preach in public<lb/> frequently.  If you will occasionally help<lb/> me with understanding&#44; it will be accounted<lb/> as a great Mitzvah to you.  I hope that<lb/> in this way I shall not interrupt my<lb/> constant preoccupation in the study of<lb/> our sacred Torah.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I remain as ever your true friend<lb/> and well&#45;wisher.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Abraham Reis</persName></p>
		</body>
